					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You're more likely to "get away with" an odd-sized ROM for CHR than for PRG because CHR has no requirement for vectors to be in a valid bank.
<br />
<br />If you're making an emulator: It's probably safest to treat "missing" banks in an odd-sized iNES ROM as mirrors of the last bank. At least that will get the vectors in the right place.</div>

