<br />I'm assuming this uses an obscure mapper that's aware of the existence of the 3 chips, but each one is still a power of 2 big.
<br />
<br />MMC3 boards have 2 ROMs (or 1, if it uses CHR-RAM), each ones is a power of 2 big. MLT-ACTION52 boards have 4 ROMs, each one is a power of 2 big. He's working on a MMC3 game, so he'd better make the sizes of those ROMs powers of 2 if he expects it to work without problems anywhere.</div>

